reporting-org.narrative: The Global Fund to Fight AIDS, Tuberculosis and Malaria

description.narrative: Guinea-Bissau suffers from a generalized lack of resources to provide adequate social services to its population. The health sector faces serious difficulties due to the insufficient and uneven distribution of health professionals and the inadequacy of financial resources and of available clinical techniques. The HIV and AIDS pandemic has emerged as a public health issue in the country. The program supported by this grant aims to decrease trends of HIV infection in the general population; improve living conditions for people living with HIV and AIDS; provide complete and reliable strategic information on the trends of the epidemic to decision making and resource allocation; and involve all HIV and AIDS partners in the country to obtain a quality national response to the epidemic. The program targets people living with HIV and AIDS, pregnant women, orphans and vulnerable children and the general population.
